-- Dubai's Amlak to resume trading in H2 2014- UAE Econ Min
-- By Stanley Carvalho
-- Mon Mar 24, 2014 04:42AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, March 24 (Reuters) - Dubai's indebted mortgage lender Amlak <AMLK.DU>, whose shares have been suspended since 2008, will resume trading on Dubai's bourse in the second half of this year, the United Arab Emirates' economy minister said on Monday.

"Our target is to list the company in the second half of this year," Sultan bin Saeed al-Mansouri told reporters on the sidelines of an event in Abu Dhabi.